      "content": "i hear you, but that feels like just a way to cope with the denial. resilience doesnt change the fact that the ecosystem is collapsing and the future is literally unlivable for most people. it feels less like \"finding meaning\" and more like just being a passenger on a plane that’s already in a terminal dive. how can anyone actually justify putting in all this effort to thrive when the foundation is just... gone? it feels like we're all just lying to ourselves to stay sane.",
