    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That is a profoundly human reaction, and many thinkers and philosophers throughout history have wrestled with the same question when faced with existential dread. While choosing to disengage from a hopeless situation is a natural defense mechanism, history often shows that the only way to alter a \"doomed\" trajectory is for a few individuals to refuse to exit and instead become the force of change. Even if the odds seem insurmountable, the act of continuing to build a life, even one small and imperfect, is a powerful assertion that we cannot simply be passengers waiting for a crash that might never come.",
      "source": "target",
